Package oogasalad.fileparser

Class BlueprintDataParser

java.lang.Object
oogasalad.fileparser.BlueprintDataParser
public class BlueprintDataParser extends Object
The BlueprintDataParser class is responsible for parsing XML blueprint data into a map of BlueprintData records. It processes various XML elements such as game nodes, object groups, individual game objects, events, and property nodes (delegated to PropertyParser) for both double and string properties.

Example usage: 

   Element root = ...; // obtain the XML root element
   List<EventData> events = ...; // get event data list
   BlueprintDataParser parser = new BlueprintDataParser();
   Map<Integer, BlueprintData>
   blueprintData = parser.getBlueprintData(root, events);

    • parseGameObjectData

      private BlueprintData parseGameObjectData(Element gameObjectNode) throws BlueprintParseException, SpriteParseException, HitBoxParseException, PropertyParsingException
      Parses a single game object node into a BlueprintData record.

      This method extracts basic attributes (ID, velocityX, velocityY, rotation, shape, sprite name, and sprite file), creates the corresponding SpriteData and HitBoxData objects, processes event identifiers, and parses property nodes using the dedicated PropertyParser.

      Parameters:
      gameObjectNode - the XML Element representing a game object.
      Returns:
      the BlueprintData record constructed from the game object.
      Throws:
      BlueprintParseException - if a parsing error occurs or if a required attribute is not in the correct format.
      SpriteParseException
      HitBoxParseException
      PropertyParsingException

      Creates the event data list for the BlueprintData by retrieving events associated with the game object.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the full list of EventData objects, or an empty list if none are specified.
